Salubako is a gamified application that addresses the challenge of promoting local
culture and tourism through digital technology, specifically focusing on the municipality
of Tinambac, Camarines Sur, in the Bicol region. The study aims to develop a gamified
tour-themed application that serves as both an informative and entertainment platform
for users, particularly the youth aged 13 and above.

The research employed a developmental design utilizing the Software Development
Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology. The system development incorporated key architectural
components, including the User Interface (UI), dialog system, and progression mechanics
to create an immersive experience around selected Tinambac landmarks.

The key findings of the study indicated that the gamified application was highly
acceptable and effective in achieving its primary objectives. The system scored strongly
in its capacity to provide relevant information about the landmarks with an average
mean of 4.3 and was recognized as a viable tool for cultural preservation and the
promotion of local tourism with an average mean of 4.0. While the game successfully
delivered the necessary entertainment, some refinement is suggested for the core game
mechanics (e.g., puzzles and exploration) to maximize user engagement.

The study concluded that integrating information systems with local culture through
gamification is feasible for digital tourism promotion. The resulting application,
``Salubako,'' helped in closing the gap in the digital documentation and promotion of
provincial heritage, aligning with global goals for sustainable economic growth and
cultural preservation.

