\subsection{Game Overview}

The game follows Roberto as the main character. After experiencing deterioration in
health at his job, he was later given time off to recuperate, leading to his decision
to go back to his hometown. The player controls Roberto to explore and know more about
the setting of the game, the municipality of Tinambac in the province of Camarines Sur,
which also points the player to the main goal of this game as a gamified tour of
landmarks in Tinambac. As the game progresses, the player comes into contact with the
minigames that provide the necessary challenge for the game progression and the
interactions that trigger tasks and information relevant to both the game and the
real-life counterparts it was based on, since one of the objectives of this project is
to provide information to the player about the landmarks he is exploring. To give a
better perspective of the workings of the game, starting from running it to its core
functions, the flow of the game is shown in Figure \ref{fig:dev_process} on the next
page.

