\section{Software Development Process}

The development methodology used for this project is Agile methodology. Agile
development is widely used in game design for its flexibility and iterative approach.
It enables teams to adapt quickly to changes while delivering incremental improvements,
fostering player-focused experiences. Key practices like sprint planning, daily
stand-ups, and iterative prototypes allow teams to test and refine gameplay mechanics
throughout development.

This methodology promotes collaboration among designers, programmers, and artists while
integrating continuous feedback from stakeholders and QA teams. By addressing challenges
incrementally, Agile minimizes risks and avoids costly late-stage revisions, making it
an effective framework for creating dynamic and engaging games.

Core practices and benefits include: (1) Sprint planning and daily stand-ups that
ensure alignment and progress; (2) Iterative builds that enable early gameplay testing
and refinement; (3) Continuous feedback loops that incorporate stakeholder and QA input
seamlessly; and (4) Collaboration that encourages cohesive teamwork across disciplines.
The game engine used is the Unity game engine using C\# language scripting, while the
game art style is a pixel art style.

